<P>
   JAPAN-GOLD-RUSH (Tokyo) _ The Great Japan Money Rush is on. With
$9 trillion in private savings up for grabs, international banks
and money managers are hurtling into Tokyo to stake their claims.
Japan's ``big bang'' market liberalization, which began in April,
is breaking down the barriers and luring in the likes of Travelers
Group Inc., which this week bought a 25 percent share of Nikko
Securities, the country's third-largest brokerage. By Sheryl
WuDunn.
