Orange County, Calif., shocked the world of finance and filed for
bankruptcy to the announcement this week that Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co.
had agreed to pay $400 million to settle litigation for its role in
that matter, Merrill Lynch has maintained its innocence. By Leslie
Wayne with Andrew Pollack.
</P>
<P>
