   CIR-SHREDDER (Undated) _ So you're thinking about buying a
shredder. What questions might you want to ask yourself?
Photo/Graphic. By Mickey Meece.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-ATM-SAFEGUARDS (Undated) _ It is a fantasy for modern times:
You ask an automated teller machine for $100 from your account and
like a slot machine showing three cherries, it just keeps spitting
out money. Alas, such a scene is extremely unlikely, ATM
manufacturers say. The machines contain a series of safeguards to
make sure that only the exact amount of money requested is
dispensed. Color Graphic. By Henry Fountain.
</P>
<P>
   CIRCUITS-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ Where can I find the commands to make
my screen icons bigger? By J.D. Biersdorfer.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-SCREEN-SAVERS (Undated) _ PC desktop customizing has come a
long way since the old days, when the definition of a mind-bending
screen saver was something that projected images of tropical fish
swimming languidly. Today's theme programs take various components
of your desktop _ the wallpaper, the screen saver, fonts, icons,
sounds _ and repackage them around a single theme. By Michelle
Slatella.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-COMPUTER-TRAVEL (Undated) _ Never has the life of an
armchair traveler been so exhausting. Travel sites crowd the Web.
Guidebooks to anyplace with a name and a scenic overlook jam
bookstore shelves. Who needs to pack a suitcase any more? There are
far cheaper ways to get that exotic view. By Suzanne Macneille.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-SIX-DEGREES (Undated) _ Six degrees of separation, the
theory that everyone on the planet is connected by a chain of only
six people, carries the grace of logic and the tantalizing lure of
being impossible to disprove. &QL; 
The idea of six degrees of separation has also come to the Web in
the form of a networking site called Six Degrees
(www.sixdegrees.com). By Shelly Freierman.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-HORSE-RACING (Undated) _ Horseplayers are by nature second
guessers. In 1994, a group of racing fans who had been second
guessing the sport's leading trainers and owners regularly on an
internet mailing list decided to see if they could do better. Soon,
they had pooled their money, bought a horse, and joined the game.
by Victor Mather.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-STUDENT-FEEDBACK (Undated) _ Teachers, of course, make their
living grading students. But with a device known as a Perception
Analyzer, students can now turn the tables (or the lecterns) on
their teachers and grade their performance. By Adam Bryant.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NYT News Service &LR;  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
