</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-BULLS-RODMAN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURY HAMPERS RODMAN'S EFFECTIVENESS 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 By SELENA ROBERTS   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY _ The Bulls' enigmatic Dennis Rodman became a
curiosity once again. After Coach Phil Jackson spent three days
pumping up his enigmatic forward to play well against Karl Malone,
Rodman surfaced from the locker room with a mystery injury on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson had planned to start Luc Longley on Malone, and bring
Rodman off the bench to irritate the Jazz star in Game 1 of the
finals. But because of strained ligaments in his right thumb,
Rodman's ability to bother Malone was in question. Rodman had
energy against a cold-shooting Malone at times, but he was not his
usual self, at least at first.
</P>
<P>
   He was very hesitant in going for rebounds, not wanting to stick
his right hand into the fray. But the more Malone struggled, the
more Rodman got into the mix. Rodman played a key role in keeping
the Bulls in this game down the stretch. He leaped up to slap a
fingeroll by Malone away with two minutes left in regulation, using
his right hand.
</P>
<P>
   Then in overtime, Rodman's intellect came through when he called
for a timeout while Longley was tied up for a loose ball. That
saved the Bulls a possession. Rodman also had a steal on John
Stockton.
</P>
<P>
   All of this effort kept Malone in check. He was an awful 9 of 25
from the floor, but did have 14 rebounds. It was left to Stockton
to make the game-breaking basket, as he hit a runner with 9.3
second left in overtime. In the end, Malone still out-muscled
Rodman to several rebounds, but Rodman grabbed 10 and helped the
Bulls stay close.
</P>
<P>
   Although there was no mention of Rodman's injury until game
time, it apparently occurred in Game 7 of the Bulls' series-ending
win against Indiana.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to be able to rebound like I want to,'' Rodman
said before the game. ``I can't grab the ball.''
</P>
<P>
   It almost seemed like Rodman was planting an excuse. Rodman
struggled against Malone in last year's final and was unable to
force Malone out of position and get around his bulky frame for
rebounds. Even so, the Bulls were counting on Rodman this time.
Michael Jordan made that clear, as did Scottie Pippen.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be very big for us if he can do well,'' Pippen
said. ``We need him to play at the level that we know he can. We
need him to get back to that.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman was needed right away after Longley found himself in foul
trouble early. But where was Rodman? With 4 minutes 3 seconds left
in the first quarter, Jackson searched for Rodman. But he was in
the locker room working out, and did not expect to be needed so
soon. Jackson had to go to Dickey Simpkins until Rodman surfaced a
few seconds later.
</P>
<P>
   Once in the game, Rodman was not especially effective, but
Malone was not taking advantage of the mismatch. Malone seemed to
be rusty after a 10-day layoff leading up to this game. He had no
rhythm, and hit just 3 of 8 shots in the first half.
</P>
<P>
   Rodman was the benefactor of Malone's frustrations, and was able
to sneak around him down the stretch for a couple of rebounds.
Rodman smiled at Malone's inability to score. This matchup was
working out much better than he expected. Suddenly, his thumb
didn't seem such a hindrance.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
