<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-04 02:02 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3415 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBN-DODGERS-UNEDITED-     06-04 0727
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-UNEDITED-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RUSSELL, CLAIRE ON A HIGH WIRE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)SLANG 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Los Angeles Dodgers circus added another
sideshow Wednesday with manager Bill Russell and executive vice
president Fred Claire possibly perched on the high wire.
</P>
<P>
   Less than 24 hours after the Randy Johnson trade was killed with
the Seattle Mariners, published reports from New York said Russell
and Claire will be fired at the end of the season and replaced by
Florida Marlins manager Jim Leyland and general manager Dave
Dombrowski.
</P>
<P>
   Although Fox's News Corp., the club's new owners, denied the
report that appeared in the Fox-owned New York Post, the Dodgers
once again are wading through turmoil.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is enough to worry about without all this,'' Russell
said before his team beat the the St. Louis Cardinals 7-4 in front
of 35,647 at Dodger Stadium. ``Everybody knows we will be
re-evaluated at the end of the season. Right now we're just hoping
to get everyone's focus back on the field.''
</P>
<P>
   Since Monday, the Dodgers have designated former top-pitcher
Hideo Nomo for assignment and told the Mariners they would not
trade Darren Dreifort for Johnson, one of baseball's top pitchers.
</P>
<P>
   Before Tuesday's game, Claire addressed the team to discuss the
Johnson-trade talks, which were lengthy and distracting. Claire
also attempted to reaffirm with players that he is in charge of the
baseball operation. In the May 15 blockbuster trade with Florida,
Fox Television head Chase Carey was the point man in the
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
   Now this.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're trying to get things settled down so this is not
beneficial,'' Claire said. ``(New club president Bob Graziano)
talked to me after the story came out to tell me it was not true
and I know he also talked to Bill.''
</P>
<P>
   Once again, Wednesday's game was almost an afterthought. But not
to Eric Karros, who had a home run, three singles and drove in five
runs as the Dodgers (28-30) ended a losing streak at four games.
</P>
<P>
   For Karros, the focus of trade speculation last winter, it was
his first home run and RBI since May 19. The home run came on the
first pitch of the fifth inning against Cardinals starter Mark
Petkovsek (3-2).
</P>
<P>
   Karros' big night made a winner of Ramon Martinez (7-2), who now
has victories in seven of his last eight decisions. Martinez
pitched seven innings, allowing five hits and two runs with six
strikeouts and five walks.
</P>
<P>
   Speculation has been swirling since the team was sold in late
March that no one would be safe after Fox took over.
</P>
<P>
   Russell, who turns 50 in October, is in the final season of a
two-year $700,000 contract. Claire, 62, was given a three-year
contract by former Dodgers owner Peter O'Malley several months
before the sale was finalized.
</P>
<P>
   The future of both men with the club is believed to hinge on the
club's success this year. The Dodgers have not won a post-season
game since 1998. But Fox said Wednesday there have been no talks
about replacing anyone.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is no truth to this,'' said Fox spokesman Vince Wladika
``This is obvious speculation on the part of anyone who knows the
situation in Florida. It's not true.''
</P>
<P>
   Leyland, who last season led the Marlins to a World Series
champion then watch management dismantle the club in a payroll
purge, has a multi-year contract worth $1.5 million this year. He
can opt out of the contract after this season for $500,000.
</P>
<P>
   ``My wife called me this morning and told me she heard this on
the Regis and Kathy (Lee) show,'' Leyland told the Miami Herald.
``I asked when this was supposed to happen and when was I going to
be informed. I've never talked to anybody. I don't want to talk to
anybody. It annoys me because it doesn't look good. It hurts my
feelings. I've got a job. I don't want another job. It's an insult
to another manager.''
</P>
<P>
   Because Leyland and Dombrowski are under contract, they can not
be contacted by another club without violating baseball's tampering
laws.
</P>
<P>
   Graziano said he did not think the story carried extra weight
because it was reported in a newspaper run by the owner of his
team.
</P>
<P>
   ``Rupert Murdoch owns a lot of companies and I don't think they
are all in sync to the point where he would use one entity to talk
about another.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
