<P>
   In honor of that intrepid seafarer Vasco da Gama and his journey
to India 500 years ago, the Portuguese have organized celebrations
the likes of which have never been seen in this onetime imperial
capital. On May 22, Lisbon opened the gates to Expo '98, with a
record participation of 154 countries and the theme ``The Oceans, a
Heritage for the Future.'' Marvine Howe, a former New York Times
correspondent who visits Portugal every year, reports on where to
go, what to see, where to eat ...
