<P>
   MEXICO-DRUGS _ MEXICO CITY _ Mexican officials admitted Thursday
that U.S. officials had notified them about a major
money-laundering sting before it was carried out, but without
notifying Mexico, said they had not approved of the action.
(Ferriss, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TIANANMEN _ HONG KONG _ Shielding their candles from a
punishing rain, thousands of demonstrators held the first vigil on
Chinese soil Thursday night for their countrymen mowed down in the
Tiananmen Square democracy movement nine years ago. In a ceremony
dramatized by thunder and lightening amid the sweet, sad tones of
traditional Chinese music, a crowd that organizers estimated to
number 40,000 carried off a peaceful rally in Victoria Park.
Pro-democracy activists laid wreaths in memory of the victims. It
was the first memorial to the Tiananmen victims since Hong Kong was
restored to Chinese rule last summer, and thus the first such event
ever to take place in China. (Kunstel, Cox News Service).
</P>
