   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   WOMEN-ADDICTION _ WASHINGTON _ Nearly 3 million older women in
America are addicted to prescription drugs and 2 million abuse or
are addicted to alcohol, yet their conditions go largely
undiagnosed and untreated, according to a study released Thursday.
(Lipman, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   RETIREMENT-SAVE _ WASHINGTON _ President Clinton and House
Speaker Newt Gingrich addressed concerns over whether Social
Security will be around for the baby boom generation at a
``summit'' Thursday. But some reform groups argued that reform
should begin in the Congress and White House, where retirement
benefits are excessive. (Malone, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-PRAYER _ WASHINGTON _ The House votes on a constitutional
amendment that would guarantee the right to school prayer.
(Moscoso, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-ENVIRO _ WASHINGTON _ Over 90 percent of the people of
Greece and 87 percent of Argentinians thing environmental laws in
their countries ``do not go far enough.'' In fact, majorities in
almost all of the world's most populous countries think
environmental protection is inadequate, according to a series of
polls released Thursday. Only in Finland and Nigeria did less than
half of poll respondent agree with the statement that environmental
laws ``don't go far enough.'' (Nesmith, Cox News Service 400).
</P>
<P>
   HOLOCAUST-VICTIMS _ WASHINGTON _ A Senate subcommittee approved
a bill Thursday aimed at recovering assets belonging to Holocaust
victims as well as committing the United States to join research
efforts on the topic. Central to this issue is how other countries
will proceed, since at least five neutral countries during World
War II fed the Nazi war effort by supplying key materials to
Germany, according to an interagency task force report discussed
Thursday. (Abulhassan, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   YORKTOWN _ WASHINGTON _ The National Geographic Society holds a
news conference to release photos and video footage of the U.S.S.
Yorktown, the aircraft carrier discovered on May 19 more than three
miles under the Pacific Ocean. Speakers include Robert Ballard,
expedition leader and discoverer of Titanic. (Nesmith, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   TOBFOES _ A family feud is under way among anti-tobacco forces,
pitting traditional groups like the Lung Assoc. and the American
Cancer Society against newer groups like Campaign for a Tobacco
Free Society which seem to be in favor with the Clinton
administration. (Carr, Cox News Service).
</P>
