<P>
   TOBACCO-LAWYERS (Washington) _ Lawyers who fought the tobacco
industry have found a new focus for their energies: fighting for
their share of the spoils from lawsuits against the industry. With
billions of dollars in fees at stake, lawyers who represent states
and smokers have been stalking the halls of Congress, and hiring
their own lobbyists, to insure that any tobacco legislation enacted
this year protects their fees, some reaching staggering sums.
