   &UR; NATIONAL GENERAL &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   MD-TROOPER-SUIT (Baltimore) _ The ACLU files a class-action suit
accusing Maryland state troopers of targeting blacks and Hispanics
along I-95 in efforts to cut down on drug and gun traffic along the
corridor. By Michael Janofsky.
</P>
<P>
   OKLA-BOMB-NICHOLS (Denver) _ Terry Nichols has one last chance
to reveal whether he knows more about the Oklahoma City bombing
plot before he is sentenced for his role in the deadliest terrorist
act ever on U.S. soil. If he talks _ and actually says something _
U.S. District Judge Richard Matsch might be persuaded to give him a
lighter sentence. Nichols, 43, was to return to court today for a
hearing and a final opportunity to speak before Matsch imposes a
sentence. (Hearing begins at 4:30 EDT.) By Jo Thomas.
</P>
<P>
   OLDER-WOMEN-DRUGS (Undated) _ Abuse of alcohol and prescription
drugs by older women is a hidden epidemic costing the country $30
billion a year in health care, according to a major study to be
released Thursday and separate interviews with women as old as 88
years who became addicted in California, Minnesota, Florida and New
York. By Christopher S. Wren.
</P>
<P>
   NY-BUDGET (New York) _ The City Council plans to defy the Mayor
by passing its own budget, ending a recent tradition of relative
harmony on the city's fiscal front. By Norimitsu Onishi.
</P>
<P>
   TWA-CRASH-DISPOSAL (Washington) _ The National Transportation
Safety Board this weekend begins the tough job of disposing of
personal effects of passengers from the TWA flight 800 crash,
including teddy bears, hairpieces and blue jeans. By Matthew L.
Wald.
</P>
<P>
