<HEADLINE>
A LOOK A TWO POPULAR RELATIONSHIP GUIDES  
 (WITH DATING-RULES) 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By TERESA TALERICO  
 c.1998 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Men are the hunters, the aggressors of the dating world, so let
them take the lead, say the female authors of ``The Rules.''
</P>
<P>
   Hey, guys get tired of the pressure to approach women. Confident
women of the '90s should feel free to initiate contact, says the
trio of guys who penned ``What Men Want.''
</P>
<P>
   Here's a look at these two popular relationship guides and their
dueling dating tips for women:
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``Don't talk to a man first or ask him to dance.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``Men appreciate it when women are willing and
able to make the firt move.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``Don't stare at men. ... It is never necessary to
make eye contact.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``Eye contact can be a very effective way to
convey your interest.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``Most men are not shy, just not really, really
interested if they don't approach you.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``It is easier for a man to take a swing at a guy
twice his size, ask his boss for a raise, and run a marathon on a
hot day than it is for him to approach a woman ... it is the woman
we really want to meet who makes us tongue-tied.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``Sometimes game playing is good.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``Men are turned off by women who play hard to
get.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``Don't call him and rarely return his calls.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``Calling a man first after the initial meeting
can score major points.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``On the date itself, be quiet and reserved. ...
He'll think you're interesting and mysterious.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``Don't believe that being hard to please or
mysteriously distant wins a man's affection.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``Don't be surprised if a man takes a week or two
after the first date to call. He may have a lot of things going
on.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``If we like a woman, we will call her within a
week _ and more likely in the next two or three days. If a man
doesn't call you within the first week, forget him.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``Remember, let him take the lead. He declares love
first, just as he picks most of the movies, the restaurants and the
concerts the two of you go to.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``Men will take advantage of women who let
them.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``When a man calls you, don't stay on the phone for
more than 10 minutes. Buy a timer if you have to.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``If you like him, there is no reason to hide it
or try to get the upper hand. Forget playing hard to get.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rules: ``Don't initiate sex. Biologically, the man must
pursue the woman.''
</P>
<P>
   What Men Want: ``A man wants a woman with sexual power. ... She
knows when it is her turn to lead.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-04-98 1427EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
