<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IT'S HARD NOT TO BOGART THE OREOS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: On an old episode of ``Ellen,'' one of the characters said,
``Don't bogart the Oreos!'' What is the derivation of the verb
``bogart''?
</P>
<P>
   _ B.T., Los Angeles
</P>
<P>
   A: To ``bogart'' means to act in a bold, aggressive manner or to
hog something instead of sharing it.
</P>
<P>
   The Dictionary of Regional English defines it as ``muscling into
someone's personal space,'' and states that it was popular
African-American slang during the '70s.
</P>
<P>
   The other meaning usually applies to things you can smoke.
</P>
<P>
   The inspiration for both expressions appears to be Humphrey
Bogart, an actor whose characters were known for boldness and an
ever-present cigarette.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How can I get information on space camps held for children?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.L.P., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: Space camps, simulated astronaut training for children in
grades four through seven, take place at three locations:
Titusville, Fla.; Huntsville, Ala.; and Mountain View, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   The five-day camps cost $675, and limited scholarships and
payment plans are available.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call the U.S. Space and Rocket Center at
(800) 637-7223 or visit the World Wide Web site www.spacecamp.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Some years ago I met Rosemary Clooney and found that we both
came from the Guilfoyle clan in Ireland. Where can I write to send
her some research I did?
</P>
<P>
   _ L.M., Fort Myers, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Clooney in care of Concord Records, Box 845,
Concord, CA 94522.
</P>
<P>
   The singer celebrated her 70th birthday May 23 after a busy
year. She released a new album, ``Mothers &AMP; Daughters,'' and
married longtime companion Dante DiPaolo in November.
</P>
<P>
   Her World Wide Web site is www.clooney.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
