<SLUG> BC-MURRAY-COLUMN05-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TALL TALES AND SHORT STORIES: We like mail that likes us
 &HT;    By Joe Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The readers write ...
</P>
<P>
   From Dan Rahn, the University of Georgia,
drahn(at)arches.uga.edu, on the subject of, ``We like people who
are like we are,'' as noted in a recent column:
</P>
<P>
   ``I had a 99-cent Whopper for lunch yesterday (actually a
74-cent Whopper _ when they give me a senior citizen discount
without asking, I just take it).
</P>
<P>
   ``In the line behind me was a raggedy, mean-looking woman who
was buying lunch for a raggedy, meaner-looking man and what looked
to be a family of three raggedy children with IQs lower than the
table they were sitting at.
</P>
<P>
   ``While I was waiting for my burger the man hauled off and
knocked the crap out of one of the young'uns and cussed him about
something I hadn't seen.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I got my lunch I went out to the nonsmoker, sunroom
section, grateful that I normally eat out there because there was a
wall between me and this family.
</P>
<P>
   ``But as I sat there, eating my burger and mulling my demeanor,
I wondered at how different God and I still are.
</P>
<P>
   ``He loves those people. I mostly want to avoid them. Much as I
try to be like God, I still just like people like me.''
</P>
<P>
   That's a Sunday school lesson in itself.
</P>
<P>
   From Lotilive(at)aol.com (no name listed) on the subject of
right-wing extremism:
</P>
<P>
   ``There is nothing wrong with property ownership, except when
the owner decides that destroying, wasting, polluting property is
their right. No way.
</P>
<P>
   ``Adjacent lands are affected by such actions. Governments
establish laws by which foolish acts are regulated.
</P>
<P>
   ``Your rant is extremist. You are showing how little you regard
your fellow humans by falsely claiming these kinds of individual
rights.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ultimately, every financial success is achieved collectively,
not individually.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know you don't want to hear that as you roll around in your
piles of dough, as if you created this wealth completely on your
own.
</P>
<P>
   ``The truth is the wealthy have exploited human labor to obtain
wealth. Don't pat yourself on the back as if you succeeded alone.
</P>
<P>
   ``No, you're just living in denial of how much you took
advantage of others. Maybe that is how you console your guilty
conscience.''
</P>
<P>
   For the life of me I don't know which particular rant the writer
refers to, I rant so often. As for property, I'm of the opinion
that people don't own property, property owns people. If that's
right-wing extremism, cancel my membership in the ACLU.
</P>
<P>
   From Marcus Gross, Longview, Texas, who is no right-wing
extremist:
</P>
<P>
   ``I am a Liberal Democrat. I have been married two times. Both
wives died. I am 81 years old, and I think my next wife will be
able to say, `Hallelujah, I buried the old goat!'
</P>
<P>
   ``I married a Baptist woman _ me being a Methodist _ and since
she wouldn't go to my church, I went to hers.
</P>
<P>
   ``They held me under water until I bubbled up, `I am a Baptist.'
When I got my breath back I asked the Lord to forgive me for lying.
</P>
<P>
   ``After two Baptist wives I am now back in the Methodist church,
which is not all that much different.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Baptists don't drink in front of each other. We Methodists
don't care who sees us drink.
</P>
<P>
   ``What a life.''
</P>
<P>
   And finally, a current joke making its way on the e-mail:
</P>
<P>
   What do you get when you mix Viagra and Rogaine?
</P>
<P>
   Answer: Don King.
</P>
<P>
   (Joe Murray, editor-publisher emeritus of the Lufkin (Texas)
Daily News, is senior writer for Cox Newspapers. Mailing address is
P.O. Box 151108, Lufkin, Texas 75915; e-mail is
awew18a(at)prodigy.com.)
</P>
