Thursday delivered a swift and unanimous rebuff to the request by
Kenneth Starr, the independent counsel, to shortcircuit the
ordinary appellate process and get a quick ruling by the Justices
on disputed claims of privilege for four grand jury witnesses. By
Stephen Labaton and Linda Greenhouse.
</P>
