   &UR; PLACES AND DESTINATIONS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SUMMER-HAPPENINGS-TEX (Undated) _ From Atlanta to L.A., a
roundup of film, music and art happenings this summer and beyond.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-CUP-CITY-HNS (Saint-Denis, France) _ The venue for the
1998 World Cup of Soccer will bring the eyes of the world to this
hard-working, culturally diverse industrial town of 92,000 at the
northern edge of Paris. When Saint-Denis welcomes the world, the
world will find itself already there. By Mike Greenberg.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-CUP-PARIS-HNS (Paris) _ Some Parisians care passionately
for soccer; others, perhaps most, don't. To judge from the posters
for sale in stalls and shops and subway entrances all over Paris,
the city's main passion is American film star Leonardo DiCaprio. By
Mike Greenberg.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-CUP-NOTES HNS (Paris) _ Paris always has plenty of music,
theater and dance in June and July, but the usual menu is being
expanded for the World Cup of Soccer. By Mike Greenberg.
</P>
<P>
   BELFAST-HNS (Belfast, Northern Ireland) _ Coming into Belfast,
one is struck by how small a battleground it is. Just a few streets
west of the city centre, which resembles any bustling English town,
lie the Unionist enclave Sandy Row, and the Nationalist Falls Road,
literally side by side. By John Montague and Elizabeth Wassell.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-ISLAND-COX (Daufuskie Island, S.C.) _ Daufuskie Island,
reachable only by boat, is a gentle tempo marked by tidal rhythms
and sea breezes. By Elizabeth Lee.
</P>
<P>
   MENDOCINO-HNS (San Francisco) _ Vivisting the Mendocino coast
can seem like a perpetual honeymoon, so when my sister, Susan, and
her new husband, Thomas, were married last Saturday, it made sense
that they headed straight for this promised land. By Tom Steinstra.
</P>
<P>
   CANYONHIKE-AZR (Undated) _ During my birthday party in January,
my best friend asked if I'd like to join a group hiking the Grand
Canyon in early April. My friend didn't know that turning 40 had
thrown me into a midlife crisis. Hiking the Canyon would force me
to get in shape, clear my head, give m e a goal. By Don Renfroe.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY-LANIER-COX _ (Gainesville, Ga.) _ Lake Lanier Islands
after $12 million upgrade by new owner, KSL Corp., including 30
rustic-posh rental lake houses, an excursion boat for evening
cruises and a new family water attraction, the FunDunker.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-NORMANDY-BOS (Honfleur, France) _ On a sunny summer day,
this snug little port on Normandy's Calvados Coast is a swirl of
movement and activity, filled with cheerful sounds and sensual
aromas. By William A. Davis.
</P>
<P>
   SWEDISH-SUMMER-HNS (Stockholm, Sweden) _ One of the rewards of a
harsh winter is the prospect of a brilliant summer. Nowhere is that
more true than in Sweden, where the winters can be cold and dark
and cruel, and the summers ... well, the summers are like
wildflowers _ colorful, fragrant and short-lived. By Syd Kearney.
</P>
<P>
   WALES-HNS (Llangammarch, Wales) _ At a time when much of the
world is acquiescing to Anglo-American cultural hegemony, Wales
seems to be moving in the opposite direction. From the sign that
greeted us as we crossed the River Severn bridge _ ``Croeso I
Cymru,'' ``Welcome to Wales'' _ to the red-dragon flags, it was
obvious that Wales may be part of Great Britain, but it is not part
of England. By John Flinn.
</P>
<P>
   MYSTERY-CASTLE-HNS (Phoenix) _ An 8,000-square-foot native stone
castle stands in the foothills of a mountain range 10 miles south
of downtown Phoenix. The hand-built castle remains a mystery _ even
to its princess. By Harry Shattuck.
</P>
