<P>
   1. Ever kill a guy?
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BILL'S WORLD &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Bill Tammeus, The Kansas City Star &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Lech Walesa says he may run for president of Poland again. Good.
It'll be nice to have a leader there whose name we know how to
mispronounce.
</P>
<P>
   Monica Lewinsky's new lawyers have defended folks in many
political scandals. Like war correspondents, they never run out of
work.
</P>
<P>
   The new Lewinsky lawyers are known for their ability to
negotiate deals for their clients. Imagine the products for which
they'll seek to get her endorsement contracts.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sometimes,'' Mr. Clinton says, ``when people enjoy a great
deal of success, it makes them downright dumb.'' Hence, special
prosecutors.
</P>
<P>
   Kenneth Starr says the president is ``under serious criminal
investigation.'' Which differs from the funny kind.
</P>
<P>
   Experts say the just-ended primary election in California was
almost obscenely expensive. But think what it would have cost had
the makers of ``Titanic'' been in charge.
</P>
<P>
   Jerry Brown, California's former governor who has run for
president, has been voted mayor of Oakland. He may be well on his
way to election some day to his nursing home's resident complaint
committee.
</P>
<P>
   The news about Alabama's goofball governor, Fob James, isn't as
good as we first thought. He hasn't run off. Instead, he failed to
win his primary this week and has been forced into a runoff.
</P>
<P>
   Russia's government has just sold some one-week treasury bills
to raise cash. This is like a 36-hour car loan.
</P>
<P>
   The Russians plans to use the Mir space station through 1999 and
then let it burn up in space. Odd. That's how, earlier this decade,
they also treated the old Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Clinton bumped his forehead on a White House door the other
night, leaving a red knot. Sounds like a vast right hinge
conspiracy.
</P>
<P>
   The president has ordered that new government documents be
written in plain language. Pursuant, of course, to hitherto
referenced mandates and statutes per stirps and per diem.
</P>
<P>
   ``The federal government's writing must be in plain language,''
Mr. Clinton says. Glad there was no such rule six score and 15
years ago at Gettysburg.
</P>
<P>
   Clarifying: Mr. Clinton wants plain _ not plane _ language. The
latter is what's spoken on Air Force One.
</P>
<P>
   If the GOP doesn't rein in its ``extreme right,'' says Gerald
Ford, it will lose the presidential election. What about its
extreme wrong?
</P>
<P>
   A punk rocker, Rainy Blue Cloud Greensfelder, has been running
for City Council in Nevada City, Calif. Bet that's not her real
name. Bet it's something like Rainy Blue Cloud Smith.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Clinton says the Census Bureau needs to get an accurate
count in 2000. Right, no fair counting the South Park kids or
Beavis and Butt-head.
</P>
<P>
   Experts say Russia's financial crisis is caused by an inept tax
collection system. Besides which, the ruble sounds like the name of
those tiny cars circus clowns get out of.
</P>
<P>
   American officials worry that India and Pakistan will continue
to provoke each other with nuclear developments. An arms race? What
kind of evil empires would engage in an arms race?
</P>
<P>
   Northern North Dakota received half an inch of snow the other
day. Although we haven't liked our spring heat, we'd just as soon
Fargo snow.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DAVID-LETTERMAN LATE SHOW TOP TEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Ways to Mispronounce Gwyneth Paltrow'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; As presented by actress Gwyneth Paltrow &LR;
</P>
<P>
   10. Gwyn El Nino
</P>
<P>
   9. Kenneth Starrtrow
</P>
<P>
   8. Leonardo DiPaltrio
</P>
<P>
   7. Scott Baio
</P>
<P>
   6. The Gwyneth Book of World Paltrows
</P>
<P>
   5. Gwena -- Warrior Princess
</P>
<P>
   4. Mrs. David Letterman
</P>
<P>
   3. Winning Free Throw
</P>
<P>
   2. Gwwwwwwyyyyyyyyynnthththththththththth Paltrow
</P>
<P>
   1. Punky Brewster
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PUNS ... BAD AND WORSE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Two Eskimos sitting in a kayak were chilly, but when they lit a
fire in the craft it sank--proving once and for all that you can't
have your kayak and heat it, too.
</P>
<P>
   Two boll weevils grew up in South Carolina. One went to
Hollywood and became a famous actor. The other stayed behind in the
cotton fields and never amounted to much. The second one,
naturally, became known as the lesser of two weevils.
</P>
<P>
   This guy goes into a restaurant for a Christmas breakfast while
in his home town for the holidays. After looking over the menu he
says, `I'll just have the eggs benedict.' His order comes a while
later and it's served on a big, shiny hubcap. He asks the waiter,
`What's with the hubcap?` The waiter sings, `Theres no plate like
chrome for the hollandaise!'
</P>
<P>
   A hungry lion was roaming through the jungle looking for
something to eat. He came across two men. One was sitting under a
tree and reading a book; the other was typing away on his
typewriter. The lion quickly pounced on the man reading the book
and devoured him. Even the king of the jungle knows that readers
digest and writers cramp.
</P>
<P>
   There was a man who entered a local paper's pun contest. He sent
in ten different puns,in the hope that at least one of the puns
would win. Unfortunately, no pun in ten did.
</P>
<P>
   A guy goes to a psychiatrist. `Doc, I keep having these
alternating recurring dreams. First I'm a teepee; then I'm a
wigwam;then I'm a teepee; then I'm in wigwam. It's driving me
crazy. What's wrong with me?' The doctor replies: `It's very
simple. You're two tents.'
</P>
<P>
   A woman has twins, and gives them up for adoption. One of them
goes to a family in Egypt and is named `Amal.' The other goes to a
family in Spain; they name him `Juan.' Years later, Juan sends a
picture of himself to his mom. Upon receiving the picture, she
tells her husband that she wishes she also had a picture of Amal.
Her husband responds, `But they are twins _ if you've seen Juan,
you've seen Amal.'
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Comments left on Forest Service registration sheets and comment
cards by backpackers completing wilderness camping trips: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A small deer came into my camp and stole my bag of pickles. Is
there a &QL; 
way I can get reimbursed? Please call.'
</P>
<P>
   `Escalators would help on steep uphill sections.'
</P>
<P>
   `Trails need to be wider so people can walk while holding
hands.'
</P>
<P>
   .
</P>
<P>
   `Trails need to be reconstructed. Please avoid building trails
that go uphill.'
</P>
<P>
   `Chairlifts need to be in some places so that we can get to
wonderful views &QL; 
without having to hike to them.'
</P>
<P>
   `The coyotes made too much noise last night and kept me awake.
Please .eradicate these annoying animals.'
</P>
<P>
   `A McDonald's would be nice at the trailhead.'
</P>
<P>
   `Too many rocks in the mountains.'
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE WORKPLACE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   I used to work in an orange juice factory, until I got canned.
Yeah, they put the squeeze on me, said I couldn't concentrate.
</P>
<P>
   I used to be a lumberjack, but I just couldn't hack it, so they
gave me the axe.
</P>
<P>
   I used to work in a muffler factory, until I got exhausted.
</P>
<P>
   I used to be a musician, but I wasn't noteworthy.
</P>
<P>
   I used to be a doctor, but I didn't have the patients.
</P>
<P>
   _Submitted by Linda Martinez, Ventura County Star, Ventura, CA.
</P>
