<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; 50 YEARS OF NORTH BEACH BEAUTIFICATION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   They're throwing a party  &LR; Saturday  &LR; afternoon at Parkview Beauty
Salon in North Beach to celebrate owner &UR; Joe Jachetta &LR; 's 50 years in
three locations around Washington Square. The hostesses, joining
forces to cater the event with home-cooked food, are Jachetta's
band of steadfast clients, Italian women who were of a certain age
a few years ago.
</P>
<P>
   It cost $1.50 for a wash and set on May 19, 1948, and $1.50 for
a haircut; today, it's $17.50 for a wash and set, and $15 for a
haircut, still low when compared with cutting-edge establishments.
``This shop is not a salon,'' says Jachetta. ``It's a club.'' If
you've ever seen the movie ``Steel Magnolias,'' he says, ``this is
`Steel Mortadella.' ''
</P>
<P>
   In 1948, most customers wanted to look like  &UR; Gina &LR; 
 &UR; Lollobrigida &LR; , whose hair was styled in a bouffant with spit curls.
Nowadays, although many clients are the same women, their major
demand has changed: ``They want it to last a week.'' They come in
for weekly sets _ ``at least they have it done to go to church'' _
which they preserve by wrapping their heads in toilet paper at
night, or sleeping on silk pillow cases.
</P>
<P>
   These women like to keep their hair the same color and style
that they've had for years. ``If they went home with something
new,'' says Jachetta, ``their children would say `Ma ...' ''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE PEOPLE SPEAK &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Seventeen Ohio members of Congress _ the entire delegation,
save three Republican representatives _ have sent a letter to
General Mills asking that the cereal company put a picture of
astronaut-Senator-astronaut  &UR; John Glenn &LR; , D-Ohio, on Wheaties
boxes.
</P>
<P>
   ``In a life that has been filled with service, glory and
heroism,'' said the letter, which is quoted in the Hill, ``it is
safe to say about the only thing John Glenn hasn't done and the
only honor he hasn't received is the honor of appearing on a
Wheaties box.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GETTING ELECTED AND GETTING IN THE MOVIES &LR;
</P>
