Reserves to fight in the Persian Gulf War, was played by an actor
in Showtime's ``Thanks of a Grateful Nation,'' and he was just
thankful, an aide told the Hill, that he wasn't played by  &UR; Danny &LR; 
 &UR; DeVito &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Wednesday night's AIDS benefit advance showing of
another Showtime movie,  &UR; Armistead Maupin &LR; 's ``More Tales of the
City,'' featured an actor (whose face is never seen) who seemed to
be playing a certain Oakland politician.
</P>
