<P>
   REVAMP-PROPOSAL (Los Angeles) _ Saying the public is demanding
``closer-to-home local governance,'' San Fernando Valley civic
leader David Fleming, a leader of the movement to study Valley
secession, announced a sweeping proposal for reorganizing city
government. It would form 15 semi-autonomous zones, each with an
elected council, roughly paralleling the current 15 City Council
zones. By Patrick McGreevy. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   ELWAY-STADIUM (Los Angeles) _ When John Elway walked the halls
of suburban Granada Hills High School in the late 1970s, he was a
big man on campus, a stellar athlete who led the baseball team to
back-to-back city championships and the football team to the city
playoffs. The 37-year-old Denver Broncos quarterback returned to
the school this week to see the football field he played on renamed
John Elway Stadium. By Eric Moses. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   RFK-ANNIVERSARY (Los Angeles) _ Thirty years ago today, an
assassin's bullet found its mark, killing Robert F. Kennedy and
with him a certain innocence and optimism for Americans. So it's no
surprise that those who were with RFK on that tragic night are
feeling melancholy about how little has changed since June 5, 1968
_ from the fragmented state of race relations to the unresolved
controversy that still surrounds the senator's death. By Peter
Hartlaub. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
news files.)
</P>
