<P>
   STADIUM-NAME (Seattle) Safeco insurance company has bought
naming rights to the Seattle Mariners' new $417 million stadium,
which will be called Safeco Field, officials said. Mariners
president Chuck Armstrong said the club talked with more than two
dozen companies and stands to receive $1.8 million a year for 20
years, plus annual adjustments for inflation, bringing the total to
about $40 million. That's comparable to other stadium-naming deals
elsewhere in the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
   By Ed Penhale. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MARINERS-STADIUM (Seattle) The Mariners' $40 million naming
rights deal for their new stadium is more than double those for
Coors and Jacobs fields, but in the ballpark with other new
stadiums, as pro sports franchise owners scramble for new sources
of income.
</P>
<P>
   By Angelo Bruscas. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) Mariners vs. Anaheim, Kingdome.
</P>
