<SLUG> BC-PETERSEN-MAGS-MEDIA-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PETERSEN ACQUIRES INSIDE SPORTS MAGAZINE 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Petersen Cos. has purchased the magazine Inside Sports and plans
to merge it with its 51-year-old Sport magazine, the company
announced Thursday. Petersen executives declined to disclose the
terms of this latest acquisition.
</P>
<P>
   Inside Sports, founded by Newsweek in 1979 and acquired by
Century Publishing Co. in 1982, and Sport, which Petersen recently
revamped, each have a circulation of about 750,000. Both will be
published under the name Sport, beginning with the August issue,
and Petersen said it planned to raise the rate base to 1 million in
January.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to Inside Sports, Petersen recently acquired Slam,
which covers high school basketball and which Petersen says is the
No.-1-selling sports magazine on the newsstand, with a single-copy
circulation of 180,000.
</P>
<P>
   Petersen's acquisition comes at a time when competition has
intensified among sports magazines. ESPN magazine, which arrived on
newsstands in March and is aimed at readers under 30, plans to
raise its rate base _ the circulation guaranteed advertisers _ to
500,000 in August from 350,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
