<SLUG> BC-BOSNIA-U.S.-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
U.S. SUSPENDS MILITARY AID PROGRAM FOR BOSNIA
</HEADLINE>
   (ja) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The United States has suspended part of a military
aid program for Bosnia because the republic's Muslims and Croats
refuse to cooperate on even the most minor issues of joint
security, State Department officials said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The action to withhold some aid from a program known as Train
and Equip was taken to underscore Washington's belief that the
armed forces of the Bosnian federation should adopt a unified
identity, a State Department official said.
</P>
<P>
   The Bosnian military has declined to fly the new federation flag
over military installations and to use a common insignia on
uniforms. State Department officials say those steps are necessary
to establish the military's professionalism and trustworthiness
among the population.
</P>
<P>
   During the war in Bosnia-Herzegovina, the republic's Croats and
Muslims fought each other and Bosnian Serb forces. The Dayton peace
accords imposed a fragile armistice that diplomats hoped would be
sustained in part by joining the Croat and Muslim populations in
unified police and military forces. State Department officials said
the suspension would end once the Defense Ministry agreed to use
common insignia and to fly the flag.
</P>
</TEXT>
