<HEADLINE>
EXTENSION FOR BROSIUS SOUGHT 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The New York Yankees have opened preliminary
negotiations on a contract extension for Scott Brosius, the third
baseman who could become a free agent after this season. The
discussions were acknowledged by Yankees general manager Brian
Cashman and Brosius' agent, Tony Attanasio.
</P>
<P>
   Brosius, 31, is making $2.5 million this season, and if he
continues to play well _ he is batting .337, with 35 runs batted in
_ he could command great attention as a free agent. But Brosius has
stated he loves playing in New York and would be very happy to work
out an extension before year's end.
</P>
<P>
   The Yankees, too, are talking to the agent for outfielder Chad
Curtis about an extension.
</P>
</TEXT>
