<HEADLINE>
POLO JEANS LEASES SPACE 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 By NICK RAVO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Polo Jeans Co., a supplier of fashionable casual
wear, has signed a long-term lease on 43,000 square feet of space,
the entire fourth floor, at 115 Fifth Ave., in of Manhattan's
Flatiron district.
</P>
<P>
   The company, which is relocating from 595 Madison Ave., at 57th
Street, will use the space for its showroom and executive offices.
</P>
<P>
   Newmark &AMP; Company Real Estate and the Georgetown Group
represented Polo Jeans, a subsidiary of Sun Apparel.
</P>
<P>
   Newmark also subleased the 12,000 square feet that Polo Jeans is
vacating at 595 Madison to Cosmetech of Manhattan, a manufacturer
of cases and containers for cosmetics.
</P>
<P>
   Owned by B.J.W. Associates of Manhattan, 115 Fifth Ave., at the
southeast corner of 19th Street, is a combined retail and office
building. It comprises about 285,000 square feet on seven stories.
Tenants include Perry Ellis International and Victoria's Secret.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
