in Canada EXCEPT to The Toronto Globe &AMP; Mail.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-04-98 2231EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19980604.0462 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-04 22:33 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5049 &Cx1f; tab-z
r k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HOME-TEACHING-TREND-E     06-04 1452
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOME-TEACHING-TREND-ECONOMIST-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LEARNING AROUND THE KITCHEN TABLE: HOME-TEACHING GROWS  
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Fla., Ill., Mich., and Minn.)   (This excellent 1,200-word ``separate buy'' article is from the
current (week beginning 6 June 1998) Economist magazine.)  
  
 (EDITORS: We regret that this material is NOT available to clients
